 21  /--
 22  In a monoidal category, we can take the tensor product of objects, `X ⊗ Y` and of morphisms `f ⊗ g`.
 23  Tensor product does not need to be strictly associative on objects, but there is a
 24  specified associator, `α_ X Y Z : (X ⊗ Y) ⊗ Z ≅ X ⊗ (Y ⊗ Z)`. There is a tensor unit `𝟙_ C`,
 25  with specified left and right unitor isomorphisms `λ_ X : 𝟙_ C ⊗ X ≅ X` and `ρ_ X : X ⊗ 𝟙_ C ≅ X`.
 26  These associators and unitors satisfy the pentagon and triangle equations.
 27  -/
 28  class monoidal_category (C : Type u) [𝒞 : category.{v} C] :=
